| D2 | Keep ID validation regex helpers inside `paths.ts` | Co-locate: every detector that needs path assembly also needs ID validation. Avoid `src/claude-workflow/ids.ts`. |
| D3 | `WorkflowSnapshot.status` is required; rest is `?` | SPEC contract — only `runId` and `status` drive watcher behavior; other fields are display-only. Tolerant of future Claude Code additions. |
| D4 | `JournalLineParser.markLiveMode()` is explicit API rather than auto-detected | SPEC §8.1 spec language is explicit. Caller (P3 watcher) knows when initial dump completes; auto-detecting "first new line" would need extra heuristics. |
| D5 | Truncation helper inline in `journal-parser.ts`, not in `src/utils/text.ts` | YAGNI — caller-specific 100-char limit, no reuse elsewhere yet. Promote later if other places need it. |
| D6 | Dedup snapshot by raw text, not parsed structural equality | (a) cheaper, (b) avoids array-order false negatives, (c) matches SPEC §8.2 reference code. |
| D7 | `SnapshotWatcher` is NOT a `LineParser` and does NOT use `FileWatcher` | Snapshot is whole-file overwrite (not append). `FileWatcher` tracks `processedLines`/`isFirstRead` semantics that don't apply. SPEC §8.2 explicit. |
| D8 | Forward-declare `WorkflowDetectorConfig` in `types.ts` even though detector isn't built until P3 | Lets `OutputHandler`-related callers in P3 import a stable shape without P1↔P3 churn. Minimal cost. |
| D9 | Both `withWorkflowAgents: boolean` and `workflowAttach: boolean` default to `true` | SPEC §11.1 — they are the on-by-default behaviors users opt out of via `--no-...` flags. The CLI defaults land in P3/P5; P1 just defines the types. |

